    <para id="para-00006">A major political and cultural shift occurred in about 3150 BCE when Upper and Lower Egypt were unified into a single powerful kingdom. Some evidence suggests this achievement belongs to a king named <term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00012">Narmer</term>. More recent records attribute it to a king called Menes, but many scholars now believe Menes and Narmer are one and the same (<link target-id="fig-00002"/>).</para>
